&gt; 
&gt; Alex wrote:
&gt; &gt; Hi Stack,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; So are you suggesting using the CrawlController instead of a 
&gt; &gt; CrawlJobHandler in general?  I understand how it feels a 
&gt; little weird 
&gt; &gt; with the state being modified with the event queue.  If you 
&gt; could give 
&gt; &gt; me a little bit more insight on what you are suggesting.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; I was thinking there&#39;d be an &#39;atomic&#39; checkpoint that takes 
&gt; care of the 
&gt; pause, checkpoint, resume steps -- with handling for interruptions by 
&gt; operator, etc. It would live in CrawlController.  Let me try 
&gt; and work on 
&gt; this today.
&gt; 
&gt; That would leave running a timer that on a period invokes this 
&gt; overarching checkpoint.  Could be started by the CrawlController if 
&gt; appropriate config. in heritrix.properties (The timer should probably 
&gt; live in CC too).
&gt; 
&gt; What you think?
&gt; 
&gt; St.Ack
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; I agree with the logging, quick and dirty, added recently, locally.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Thanks,
&gt; &gt; Alex
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt;  &gt; On your classes:
&gt; &gt;  &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; Looks like you&#39;ve added to the crawlPaused method in your  &gt; 
&gt; &gt; CrawlJobHandler override a check to see if a request to  &gt; 
&gt; checkpoint 
&gt; &gt; has  &gt; been set and if so, you run checkpointing. 
&gt; Checkpointing runs,
&gt; &gt;  &gt; crawlCheckpoint is called in your CJH override and you set
&gt; &gt;  &gt; &#39;shouldResume&#39; to true so that when crawlPaused is 
&gt; called again after
&gt; &gt;  &gt; checkpointing has completed, you&#39;re override invokes resume
&gt; &gt;  &gt; (I like your
&gt; &gt;  &gt; use of java.util.Timer).
&gt; &gt;  &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; One suggestion I&#39;d make is that changing/managing crawler
&gt; &gt;  &gt; state should
&gt; &gt;  &gt; be done by the CrawlController rather than out of the 
&gt; state change
&gt; &gt;  &gt; methods in CJH (CrawlController is overrideable. See
&gt; &gt;  &gt; CrawlJob#setupForCrawlStart where we override CC so we can remove
&gt; &gt;  &gt; registered MBeans).
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt;  &gt; Would also suggest using a java.util logger in place of 
&gt; calls to  &gt; 
&gt; &gt; System.out.err.  &gt;
&gt; &gt;  &gt; Calling Heritrix#main is working fine for you?  Any 
&gt; reason you don&#39;t
&gt; &gt;  &gt; want to do &#39;new Heritrix()&#39; only?  Did you try it?
